Here's a one-liner to make WSL2 Ubuntu completely case-insensitive for commands, aliases, and tab completion:

```bash
echo 'set completion-ignore-case on' >> ~/.inputrc && echo 'shopt -s nocaseglob' >> ~/.bashrc && echo 'bind "set completion-ignore-case on"' >> ~/.bashrc && echo 'for cmd in $(compgen -A alias); do alias "${cmd^^}"="$(alias "$cmd" | cut -d"=" -f2-)"; done' >> ~/.bashrc && source ~/.bashrc
```

**What this does:**
- `set completion-ignore-case on` in `.inputrc` - Makes tab completion case-insensitive
- `shopt -s nocaseglob` - Makes filename globbing case-insensitive  
- `bind "set completion-ignore-case on"` - Makes command completion case-insensitive
- The `for` loop creates uppercase versions of all your aliases
- `source ~/.bashrc` - Applies changes immediately

**After running this, restart your shell or run:**
```bash
source ~/.bashrc
```

**Now these will all work:**
```bash
CC          # same as cc (clear)
LS          # same as ls
CD          # same as cd
GREP        # same as grep
```

**For making ALL commands case-insensitive (advanced):**
```bash
echo 'function command_not_found_handle() { command "${1,,}" "${@:2}"; }' >> ~/.bashrc && source ~/.bashrc
```

This makes any uppercase command automatically try the lowercase version if the uppercase doesn't exist.

**Complete one-liner for everything:**
```bash
echo 'set completion-ignore-case on' >> ~/.inputrc && echo 'shopt -s nocaseglob' >> ~/.bashrc && echo 'bind "set completion-ignore-case on"' >> ~/.bashrc && echo 'for cmd in $(compgen -A alias); do alias "${cmd^^}"="$(alias "$cmd" | cut -d"=" -f2-)"; done' >> ~/.bashrc && echo 'function command_not_found_handle() { command "${1,,}" "${@:2}"; }' >> ~/.bashrc && source ~/.bashrc
```
